{"type": "article", "id": 32054, "title": "只要书够，书架的创意就永远不嫌多｜这个设计了不起", "description": "每个周末，《好奇心日报》都会找个主题为你寻找精彩设计。", "date": "2016-09-09T23:47:43Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 2383, "name": "书架"}, {"id": 32627, "name": "Objet Optimisé"}, {"id": 247, "name": "Nendo"}, {"id": 26349, "name": "CITCO"}, {"id": 2167, "name": "Zaha Hadid"}, {"id": 6085, "name": "Sebastian Errazuriz"}, {"id": 18827, "name": "Sebastian Bergne"}, {"id": 32628, "name": "Mizuki Odashiro"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 18, "praise_count": 704, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160909222720nmdcTxUtawPZehDG.png", "contents": "<p class=\"\">「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。<br></p><p class=\"\">方方正正的书架或许是不少人藏书时的首选，然而看久了这类中规中矩的布置难免会让人感到有些乏味。实际上只要有一个稳定的结构，书架的造型完全可以脱离那些方正的格子，打造出一个不需要太过严肃的阅读空间。这周的推荐就是这些让人意想不到的书架设计。</p><h3>Bilbao by Sebastian Errazuriz</h3><p><a href=\"http://www.meetsebastian.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sebastian Errazuriz</a> 是一名来自在纽约工作的智利裔艺术家和设计师，当他在智利首都圣地亚哥的街头漫步时，一截遗落的残枝启发他制作了这款名为 <a href=\"http://www.meetsebastian.com/sebastian-errazuriz-design-art-tree-shelf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bilbao</a> 的书架，属于他依靠天然素材打造的 Tree 系列作品。Errazuriz 将残枝带回了自己的工作室，在尽量不改变残枝本身形态的基础上进行了加工，使它能够更好地贴合墙面。上完黑色哑光漆的残枝搭配黑色的不锈钢或是透明的玻璃搁板后就变成了一个精美的书架，能让人感受到自然与设计恰到好处的结合。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223057xQwH9WJFjt5mAG0P.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"png\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223057SkenZ7l3YTaoEfIW.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749333\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223058IKDwZaS9j4fGrEzv.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.749333\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223058cdnIVYZrvkW4q6xu.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Tone by Mizuki Odashiro</h3><p>谁说书架的搁板一定要硬邦邦的？日本武藏野美术大学 2015 届毕业生 Mizuki Odashiro 就利用一系列彩色的薄纱打造出了这款名为 Tone 的书架。整个设计非常简单，轻质的薄纱通过搭扣固定在黑色的金属框架上，安装和拆卸都非常方便，允许用户随意改变书架的设计。设计师采用的是比普通尼龙搭扣更结实的 3m™ dual lock™ 粘扣，它们能够让每一张薄纱承受五千克的重量——不过话说回来，感觉什么都不放就是一个很美的装置，而且书放不平的话，很多强迫症会抓狂吧。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223029dDFmfE4TNRoJWSxA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.662592\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223029IwMTE87odiR9K2Ar.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.669927\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223029f3q8Y7dPzO4tQbvS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.669927\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609092230295bofIa3RSJi4K67F.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.493888\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223029aTQoOsMz62qjL8Hu.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.669927\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909223030InumPbH4iofK7Vpj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.669927\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Valle by Zaha Hadid &amp; CITCO</h3><p>在今年的米兰家具展上，意大利石器公司 <a href=\"http://www.citco.it/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CITCO</a> 带来了与扎哈共同设计的 <a href=\"http://www.citco.it/en/collection/complements\" rel=\"nofollow\">Valle</a> 书架。Valle 包括了四个用黑色花岗岩制成的模块，材质特有的坚硬质地同扎哈代表性的轻盈线条形成了鲜明的对比。这些模块既可以独立安装也能组合在一起营造出一种奇妙的延伸感，本身也能作为一件墙面装饰品使用。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222951OdXglCVLGxD6q3Un.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222951mwUrab9eOLIntgfp.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.671149\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222951XRLQYn817NbpzgdE.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750611\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222951jaMxhfHbdZKN0l97.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.706601\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222951Rj0ohaH7iX6VA9Bt.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.718826\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222951sjw6X3meWBPaO4JD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.712714\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>nest shelf by nendo</h3><p>这个设计其实已经提过好几次了。由日本 <a href=\"http://www.nendo.jp/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">nendo</a> 工作室利用碳纤维打造的 <a href=\"http://www.nendo.jp/en/works/nest-shelf/\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">nest shelf</a> 是一个能够根据需要延伸或是收缩的灵活设计，展开的过程看起来像是有一个相同的书架从中自然生长出来似的，显得非常流畅。只需要简单的推拉动作，nest shelf 的网格结构就会在维持对称的基础上发生变化，让用户可以发挥自己的创意。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609092229189r5sbRhJTafiPBe8.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"gif\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222918ZFlidumkrShLXWa3.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222916xCIDGfBaiY7TzbUX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222916ioLaNJb62wRfurKx.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222917wfGa2Qs8toyYb6pC.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222916He6NrKOWuvAh4Ft3.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>L shelf by Objet Optimisé</h3><p>这也是一个巧妙的设计，之前也有提及。</p><p>第一眼看到 <a href=\"http://www.objetoptimise.com/en/product-l-shelf-1\" rel=\"nofollow\">L shelf</a> 的时候，你或许会因为它歪歪的模样感到紧张——不必担心，看似处于倾倒边缘的它有着非常稳定的结构。这个由 L 型弯木组件组成的书架来自法国设计师 Aurélien Veyrat 成立的 <a href=\"http://www.objetoptimise.com/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Objet Optimisé</a> 工作室，组装时无需额外使用五金零件或是胶水，完全依靠组件本身的插口彼此相连。模块设计使组件在运输或是还没有组装的情况下能够堆叠在一起，不会占据太多空间。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222846CklivUTowLEFpAXz.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222845iLhPQY6nZNRAMr7D.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222845fqEw2p8UCP5BRuy7.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222846VSn8vMEfKD0hmPsY.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222846631jSs9XNLD5xl7V.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222848RCX0pwQSjD1rP5ef.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>FICTION by Sebastian Bergne</h3><p>如果你想让你的藏书也“体验”一次失重，不妨试试英国工业设计师 <a href=\"http://www.sebastianbergne.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sebastian Bergne</a> 带来的这款名为 FICTION 书架。白色的钢板采用了类似 Z 型的结构，直立时最上方的一本有一种悬浮的效果，可以放在座椅旁随手取书。横放状态下书架则隐藏在书本下方，在白色背景下会让人产生一种书本失重的错觉。这是它的<a href=\"http://www.sebastianbergne.com/product/fiction/\" rel=\"nofollow\">购买链接</a>，售价为 78 英镑。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222802HVoa8FIgEZ3KNnzQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222803D2wVCWhPvyQtF9nl.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222803V8n5TdizEpoBXysJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222802dlNMcFPvw3gSHe2u.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2016090922280343T6wpsO2LM05Z8h.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160909222803VzZ8P6KcvfFM9ku1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}